{
  "stem": "13457.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Several houses around the house where we were-- were living in the, in the basement-- collapsed.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And people-- and hunger started.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "People were eating horses, dead horses, killed horses, from the street.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 22 SECONDS] Anyway, when the bombardment ended up, we went back to our apartment in Targowa-- on Targowa, which is, as I said, where we lived on the one flight up.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the Germans walked into Warsaw within a couple of days or the same day that we got there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I remember looking through the window, bedroom window of my parents, and I saw the first-- [PAUSES FOR 11 SECONDS] the first detachments of the German army come into Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And there were small detachments.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Of course, at-- in the evening, there was curfew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We were well-stocked with provisions, with food, because my father, as a Polish officer, was drafted few days before the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He said-- he left in the middle of the night-- partly this was the routine then-- in his already, the way I remember, military uniform.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And, and he left.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So during the siege of Warsaw, my father wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I was with my sister and, and my mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Now, when the German walked into Warsaw, there was a curfew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I remember my mother hollering every time I would make a terrible mistake and put the light on in the, in the bedroom.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Because the Germans were shooting already into the windows wherever they would see a light.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But then apparently in November sometime, there is a Polish day of independence.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And the way my, my memory tells me, the Germans, I remember, came to our apartment to look for my father.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
